beer_name: Shepherd Neame Queen Court Harvest Ale

review_blob:
Although the beer was in good condition, I seem to have fallen out of love with this beer now you can get it everywhere. I used to prefer it when you stumbled across it randomly, another example of a small brewery being bought out by a big fish. Beer may be the same, but now it's all over the place, sorry guys. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Straight from cask at The Firkin Alehouse, Folkestone, Kent. Good condition, pleasant taste, was expecting a little more though from this seasonal ale.

Straight from cask in The Firkin Alehouse, Folkestone, Kent. Beer in very good condition, lovely colour, super mouth feel, great hoppy aromas, very pleasant aftertaste.
